==Overview==
The [[Terran]] '''Claymore''' is larger and more powerful than any [[Commonwealth]] [[M8|bomber]], but its use is handicapped by the fact that it can only utilize the very rare [[Phantom Missile]]. If a decent stockpile of them can be gathered, however, the Claymore is probably the best bomber in the game, as it does not suffer the ordinance/jump energy dilemma plaguing commonwealth bombers, since it has a very spacious cargo bay and smaller missiles with relation to volume.  Their yield is actually considerably higher than that of the [[Tomahawk Heavy Missile]].

==Background==
The Claymore [[M8|bomber]] provides the [[Terran|United Space Command]] with an easily deployable and flexible strike capability.

==Physical Characteristics==
The Claymore resembles two [[Baldric]]s mated by their ventral surfaces, a big box with a wedge-shaped bow.  It is white with red trim.

== Combat ==
As with any [[M8|bomber]], the Claymore is devastating to anything [[M6]] and up while it carries ammunition. It has very poor fighter defense so it should be kept well away from enemy [[M3]] and [[M4]] class ships.

== Equipment ==
The Claymore is unique in its use of the potent [[Phantom Missile]].

